<div class="c630_1">
<div id="v630.1.1"><span class="G3972 s">Paul</span><span class="G1401 s">, a servant</span><span class="G2316 s"> of God</span><span class="G1161 s">, and</span><span class="G652 s"> an apostle</span><span class="G2424 s"> of Jesus</span><span class="G5547 s"> Christ</span><span class="G2596 s">, according to</span><span class="G4102 s"> the faith</span><span class="G2316 s"> of God's</span><span class="G1588 s"> elect</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G1922 s"> the acknowledging</span><span class="G225 s"> of the truth</span><span class="G3588 s"> which</span><span class="G2596 s"> is after</span><span class="G2150 s"> godliness</span>;</div>
<div id="v630.1.2"><span class="G1909 s">In</span><span class="G1680 s"> hope</span><span class="G166 s"> of eternal</span><span class="G2222 s"> life</span><span class="G3739 s">, which</span><span class="G2316 s"> God</span><span class="G893 s">, that cannot lie</span><span class="G1861 s">, promised</span><span class="G4253 s"> before</span><span class="G166 s"> the world</span><span class="G5550 s"> began</span>; <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (In: or, For)</span></div>
<div id="v630.1.3"><span class="G1161 s">But</span><span class="G5319 s"> hath</span><span class="G2398 s"> in due</span><span class="G2540 s"> times</span><span class="G5319 s"> manifested</span><span class="G846 s"> his</span><span class="G3056 s"> word</span><span class="G1722 s"> through</span><span class="G2782 s"> preaching</span><span class="G3739 s">, which</span><span class="G4100 s"> is committed</span><span class="G1473 s"> unto me</span><span class="G2596 s"> according to</span><span class="G2003 s"> the commandment</span><span class="G2316 s"> of God</span><span class="G2257 s"> our</span><span class="G4990 s"> Saviour</span>;</div>
<div id="v630.1.4"><span class="G5103 s">To Titus</span><span class="G1103 s">, <i>mine</i> own</span><span class="G5043 s"> son</span><span class="G2596 s"> after</span><span class="G2839 s"> the common</span><span class="G4102 s"> faith</span><span class="G5485 s">: Grace</span><span class="G1656 s">, mercy</span><span class="G1515 s">, <i>and</i> peace</span><span class="G575 s">, from</span><span class="G2316 s"> God</span><span class="G3962 s"> the Father</span><span class="G2532 s"> and</span><span class="G2962 s"> the Lord</span><span class="G2424 s"> Jesus</span><span class="G5547 s"> Christ</span><span class="G2257 s"> our</span><span class="G4990 s"> Saviour</span>.</div>
<div id="v630.1.5"><span class="G5127 s">For this</span><span class="G5484 s"> cause</span><span class="G2641 s"> left I</span><span class="G4571 s"> thee</span><span class="G1722 s"> in</span><span class="G2914 s"> Crete</span><span class="G2443 s">, that</span><span class="G1930 s"> thou shouldest set in order</span><span class="G3007 s"> the things that are wanting</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G2525 s"> ordain</span><span class="G4245 s"> elders</span><span class="G2596 s"> in every</span><span class="G4172 s"> city</span><span class="G5613 s">, as</span><span class="G1473 s"> I</span><span class="G1299 s"> had appointed</span><span class="G4671 s"> thee</span>: <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (wanting: or, left undone)</span></div>
<div id="v630.1.6"><span class="G1536 s">If any</span><span class="G2076 s"> be</span><span class="G410 s"> blameless</span><span class="G435 s">, the husband</span><span class="G3391 s"> of one</span><span class="G1135 s"> wife</span><span class="G2192 s">, having</span><span class="G4103 s"> faithful</span><span class="G5043 s"> children</span><span class="G3361 s"> not</span><span class="G1722 s"> accused</span><span class="G810 s"> G2724 of riot</span><span class="G2228 s"> or</span><span class="G506 s"> unruly</span>.</div>
<div id="v630.1.7"><span class="G1063 s">For</span><span class="G1985 s"> a bishop</span><span class="G1163 s"> must</span><span class="G1511 s"> be</span><span class="G410 s"> blameless</span><span class="G5613 s">, as</span><span class="G3623 s"> the steward</span><span class="G2316 s"> of God</span><span class="G3361 s">; not</span><span class="G829 s"> selfwilled</span><span class="G3361 s">, not</span><span class="G3711 s"> soon angry</span><span class="G3361 s">, not</span><span class="G3943 s"> given to wine</span><span class="G3361 s">, no</span><span class="G4131 s"> striker</span><span class="G3361 s">, not</span><span class="G146 s"> given to filthy lucre</span>;</div>
<div id="v630.1.8"><span class="G235 s">But</span><span class="G5382 s"> a lover of hospitality</span><span class="G5358 s">, a lover of good men</span><span class="G4998 s">, sober</span><span class="G1342 s">, just</span><span class="G3741 s">, holy</span><span class="G1468 s">, temperate</span>; <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (men: or, things)</span></div>
<div id="v630.1.9"><span class="G472 s">Holding fast</span><span class="G4103 s"> the faithful</span><span class="G3056 s"> word</span><span class="G2596 s"> as</span><span class="G1322 s"> he hath been taught</span><span class="G2443 s">, that</span><span class="G5600 s"> he may be</span><span class="G1415 s"> able</span><span class="G1722 s"> by</span><span class="G5198 s"> sound</span><span class="G1319 s"> doctrine</span><span class="G2532 s"> both</span><span class="G3870 s"> to exhort</span><span class="G2532 s"> and</span><span class="G1651 s"> to convince</span><span class="G483 s"> the gainsayers</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (asâ€¦: or, in teaching)</span></div>
<div id="v630.1.10"><span class="G1063 s">For</span><span class="G1526 s"> there are</span><span class="G4183 s"> many</span><span class="G506 s"> unruly</span><span class="G2532 s"> and</span><span class="G3151 s"> vain talkers</span><span class="G2532 s"> and</span><span class="G5423 s"> deceivers</span><span class="G3122 s">, specially</span><span class="G1537 s"> they of</span><span class="G4061 s"> the circumcision</span>:</div>
<div id="v630.1.11"><span class="G3739 s">Whose</span><span class="G1993 s"> mouths</span><span class="G1163 s"> must</span><span class="G1993 s"> be stopped</span><span class="G3748 s">, who</span><span class="G396 s"> subvert</span><span class="G3650 s"> whole</span><span class="G3624 s"> houses</span><span class="G1321 s">, teaching</span><span class="G3739 s"> things which</span><span class="G1163 s"> they ought</span><span class="G3361 s"> not</span><span class="G5484 s">, for</span><span class="G150 s"> filthy</span><span class="G2771 s"> lucre's</span><span class="G5484 s"> sake</span>.</div>
<div id="v630.1.12"><span class="G5100 s">One</span><span class="G1537 s"> of</span><span class="G846 s"> themselves</span><span class="G4396 s">, <i>even</i> a prophet</span><span class="G846 s"> of their</span><span class="G2398 s"> own</span><span class="G2036 s">, said</span><span class="G2912 s">, The Cretians</span><span class="G104 s"> <i>are</i> alway</span><span class="G5583 s"> liars</span><span class="G2556 s">, evil</span><span class="G2342 s"> beasts</span><span class="G692 s">, slow</span><span class="G1064 s"> bellies</span>.</div>
<div id="v630.1.13"><span class="G3778 s">This</span><span class="G3141 s"> witness</span><span class="G2076 s"> is</span><span class="G227 s"> true</span><span class="G1223 s">. Wherefore</span><span class="G1651 s"> G3739 G156 rebuke</span><span class="G846 s"> them</span><span class="G664 s"> sharply</span><span class="G2443 s">, that</span><span class="G5198 s"> they may be sound</span><span class="G1722 s"> in</span><span class="G4102 s"> the faith</span>;</div>
<div id="v630.1.14"><span class="G3361 s">Not</span><span class="G4337 s"> giving heed</span><span class="G2451 s"> to Jewish</span><span class="G3454 s"> fables</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G1785 s"> commandments</span><span class="G444 s"> of men</span><span class="G654 s">, that turn from</span><span class="G225 s"> the truth</span>.</div>
<div id="v630.1.15"><span class="G2513 s">Unto the pure</span><span class="G3956 s"> all things</span><span class="G3303 s"> <i>are</i> pure</span><span class="G1161 s"> G2513: but</span><span class="G3392 s"> unto them that are defiled</span><span class="G2532 s"> and</span><span class="G571 s"> unbelieving</span><span class="G3762 s"> <i>is</i> nothing</span><span class="G2513 s"> pure</span><span class="G235 s">; but</span><span class="G2532 s"> even</span><span class="G846 s"> their</span><span class="G3563 s"> mind</span><span class="G2532 s"> and</span><span class="G4893 s"> conscience</span><span class="G3392 s"> is defiled</span>.</div>
<div id="v630.1.16"><span class="G3670 s">They profess</span><span class="G1492 s"> that they know</span><span class="G2316 s"> God</span><span class="G1161 s">; but</span><span class="G2041 s"> in works</span><span class="G720 s"> they deny</span><span class="G5607 s"> <i>him</i>, being</span><span class="G947 s"> abominable</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G545 s"> disobedient</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G4314 s"> unto</span><span class="G3956 s"> every</span><span class="G18 s"> good</span><span class="G2041 s"> work</span><span class="G96 s"> reprobate</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (reprobate: or, void of judgment)</span></div></div>
